To tackle this issue without using a premium plugin, you can add a custom code snippet to your WooCommerce store that will convert the currency to EGP during the checkout process. Before proceeding, please make sure to back up your website, as custom code can sometimes cause unexpected issues.

Add the following code snippet to your theme's `functions.php` file:

```php
add_action( 'woocommerce_before_calculate_totals', 'convert_currency_to_egp', 10, 1 );

function convert_currency_to_egp( $cart ) {
    if ( is_admin() && ! defined( 'DOING_AJAX' ) ) return;

    // Set the exchange rate for USD to EGP (update this value regularly)
    $exchange_rate = 31.07;

    // Loop through the cart items
    foreach ( $cart->get_cart() as $cart_item_key => $cart_item ) {
        $product = $cart_item['data'];

        // If the product price is in USD, convert it to EGP
        if ( get_option( 'woocommerce_currency' ) == 'USD' ) {

            $egp_price = $product->get_price() * $exchange_rate;
            $product->set_price( $egp_price );

            // Update the cart item currency to EGP
            $cart_item['line_total'] = $cart_item['line_total'] * $exchange_rate;
            $cart_item['line_subtotal'] = $cart_item['line_subtotal'] * $exchange_rate;
        }
    }
}
```

This code snippet will automatically convert the currency back to EGP during the checkout process if your store's currency is set to USD. Make sure to update the `$exchange_rate` variable regularly to match the current exchange rate.

For displaying prices in USD in the frontend, you can use a lightweight currency switcher like "WOO Multi Currency Lite" or "WooCommerce Currency Switcher (free version)," and set it to show prices in USD instead of EGP.

Note: Custom coding is offered "as-is" and might require tweaking to achieve the exact desired outcome. Additionally, when you update the theme or switch to another theme, you might lose the custom code added to the `functions.php` file. So it's a good practice to create a child theme or use a custom plugin to implement the custom code.

If you still face any issues, it's recommended to hire a developer or find a suitable alternative plugin.

